revision.text:
{{about| the cancer research award | the film prize | Alfred P. Sloan Prize}} The '''Alfred P. Sloan Jr. Prize''' was a $250,000 award given by the General Motors Cancer Research Foundation for outstanding oncological research.<ref name="Cancer Research 1999 pp. 1673s–1673s">{{cite journal | title=Laureates: General Motors Cancer Research Awards | journal=Cancer Research | volume=59 | issue=7 Supplement | date=1 March 1999 | issn=0008-5472 | pages=1673s | url=http://cancerres.aacrjournals.org/content/59/7_Supplement/1673s | access-date=20 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gm.com/company/gmability/philanthropy/cancer_research/prize.htm |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070313231403/http://www.gm.com/company/gmability/philanthropy/cancer_research/prize.htm |title=GM Cancer Previous Prize Winners |publisher=General Motors |archivedate=13 March 2007 |accessdate=12 August 2012 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>
The prize was awarded annually from 1979 to 2005. Of the winners, 15 out of 37 have gone on to win either a [[Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine]] or a [[Nobel Prize in Chemistry]].
in 2006, due to budget constraints, the Alfred P. Sloan Jr. prize, the [[Kettering Prize|Charles K. Kettering]] prize, and the [[Charles S. Mott Prize]] were consolidated into a single General Motors Cancer Research Award which also had a value of $250,000.<ref>{{cite web | title= Public Awareness Of Cancer Research: The Driving Force Behind GM's Awards / | url=http://classic.the-scientist.com/?articles.view/articleNo/12040 }}</ref> The first and only winner of the General Motors Cancer Research Award was [[Napoleone Ferrara]].<ref>{{cite journal|author=Jones A |year= |title=Napoleone Ferrara wins 2006 GM Cancer Research Award |url=https://www.landesbioscience.com/journals/cbt/article/3155/ |journal=Cancer Biology & Therapy |volume=5 |issue=7 |pages=708–709 |doi=10.4161/cbt.5.7.3155 |pmid=17022136 |date=July 2006 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140202190919/https://www.landesbioscience.com/journals/cbt/article/3155/ |archivedate=2014-02-02 }}</ref>
After 2006 no more prizes were awarded.{{citation needed|date=August 2012}}
