'''Pakistanis in Iraq''' are mostly workers contracted and consigned to various construction companies, most of which are [[Kuwait]]i.<ref>[http://www.brecorder.com/index.php?show=detail&id=50972&currPageNo=1&query=&search=&term=&supDate= Iraq not safe to visit: foreign office], ''[[Business Recorder]]''{{dead link|date=February 2013}}</ref> The number of these workers, as projected by the ''[[Overseas Pakistanis Foundation]]'' and various other sources, equals approximately 400.<ref>[http://www.opf.org.pk/download/anual/YEARBK.pdf Overseas Pakistanis Foundations - Yearbook (2004-2005)] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100524170403/http://www.opf.org.pk/download/anual/YEARBK.pdf |date=May 24, 2010 }}</ref> In recent times, Pakistani [[expatriates]] have seen growing threats to safety. The controversial killings of two Pakistanis in Iraq in 2005 led to high tensions between the two countries, with the [[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Pakistan)|Foreign Affairs Ministry of Pakistan]] banning all visas for Pakistanis to Iraq and insisting that all Pakistani nationals vacate Iraq.<ref>[http://www.dawn.com/2004/08/01/top4.htm FO says 400 Pakistanis in working in Iraq], [[Dawn News]] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20050312202821/http://www.dawn.com/2004/08/01/top4.htm |date=March 12, 2005 }}</ref>

